📄 PRODUCT REQUIREMENTS DOCUMENT (PRD)

Product Name: ArthaPath Nepal
Version: 1.0
Document Type: Product Requirements Document
Product Type: Web-based Fintech Investment Intelligence Platform
Market: Nepal

1. Product Overview
1.1 Vision

Build a web-based investment intelligence platform that helps Nepali citizens make structured, risk-aware, long-term investment decisions using data modeling and AI-assisted explanations.

The product provides allocation suggestions, projections, and educational insights. It does NOT execute trades and does NOT provide licensed financial advice.

2. Problem Statement

Most Nepali youth:

Only know IPO and secondary stock trading.

Keep money in low-interest savings accounts.

Lack structured understanding of risk, diversification, and compounding.

Do not know capital allocation strategies based on time horizon and risk tolerance.

There is no centralized platform in Nepal providing:

Structured investment discovery

Risk-based allocation modeling

Compounding simulation

Scenario projections

3. Goals & Objectives
3.1 Primary Goals

Increase financial literacy among Nepali youth.

Provide structured allocation recommendations.

Encourage long-term disciplined investing.

Provide realistic projections (not speculative promises).

3.2 Non-Goals

Trade execution

Real-time stock speculation

Day-trading signals

Price prediction guarantees

Personalized certified financial advisory

4. Target Users
4.1 Primary Users

Age: 18–35

Location: Nepal

Capital: NPR 5,000 – NPR 1,000,000

Beginner to intermediate investors

4.2 Secondary Users

Remittance earners

Salaried professionals

Small business owners

5. Core Features (MVP)
5.1 User Financial Input Module

User inputs:

Total investment capital (required)

Monthly recurring investment (optional)

Investment duration (years)

Risk tolerance (Low / Medium / High)

Liquidity need (Low / Medium / High)

Emergency fund status (Yes/No)

Validation:

Numeric validation

Range constraints

Required field enforcement

5.2 Risk Classification Engine

System calculates:

Risk score based on:

Time horizon

Liquidity need

Risk tolerance

Outputs:

Conservative

Balanced

Aggressive profile

Must be deterministic and rule-based.

5.3 Investment Knowledge Database

Structured internal database including:

For each investment category:

Name

Category (Stocks, Mutual Fund, Bond, FD, Gold, Real Estate, Business)

Expected annual return range

Risk level

Liquidity score

Minimum capital requirement

Lock-in period

Regulation authority

Description

Historical reference performance (if available)

Data initially curated manually.

5.4 Allocation Engine

Based on:

Risk profile

Duration

Capital amount

System calculates:

Percentage allocation across investment types

Capital distribution per category

Diversification logic

Output example:

40% Mutual Funds

30% Stocks

20% Fixed Deposit

10% Gold

No individual stock recommendations in MVP.

5.5 Investment Projection Engine

System calculates:

Using compound interest formula:

Conservative projection

Expected projection

Optimistic projection

Includes:

Initial capital

Monthly contribution

Time horizon

Variable annual return rates

Outputs:

Final projected value range

Total contributions

Estimated gain

5.6 AI Explanation Layer

AI generates:

Human-readable explanation of allocation

Risk explanation

Time-horizon reasoning

Educational context

AI does NOT:

Predict stock prices

Override allocation logic

Guarantee returns

5.7 Investment Simulator

User can:

Adjust capital

Adjust monthly investment

Change duration

Change risk tolerance

System updates projections dynamically.

Includes:

Line chart for growth projection

Pie chart for allocation breakdown

5.8 Educational Module

Each investment category includes:

What it is

How it works in Nepal

Risk explanation

Pros and cons

Suitable investor profile

Worst-case scenario

Content written clearly and realistically.

6. Legal & Compliance

System must include:

Disclaimer: “This platform does not provide financial advice.”

Clear risk warnings.

No return guarantees.

No speculative stock tips.

Compliance review against SEBON and Nepal Rastra Bank regulations (future phase).

7. Data Sources

MVP:

Manually curated database

Official public data sources

Future:

Automated scraping from official financial portals

Public APIs (if available)

No anonymous web scraping for financial recommendations.

